'''
Function
A function is a block of reusable code 
that performs a specific task when called.

---
def Keyword
Used to define a function.

def greet():
    print("Hello!")

---
return Statement
Used to send back (return) a value from the function.

def add(a, b):
    return a + b

result = add(3, 4)
print(result)  # Output: 7

---
Arguments (Parameters)
Arguments are values you pass into the function.


def welcome(name):
    print("Welcome", name)
    
welcome("Ali")
____
Default Argument Value
We can give a  default value to a parameter 
so its optional when calling the function.


def welcome(name="Guest"):
    print("Welcome", name)

welcome()         # Output: Welcome Guest
welcome("Iram") # Output: Welcome Ayesha
'''

